The paper focuses on inducing analogical reasoning in neural networks that learn to perceive and reason about raw visual data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of symbolic analogy making, which falls under the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL).
